added.title: Nightmare on Toon Street
added.description: In this two-part episode, Sweetie and Buster's plan to give their friends a non-scary Halloween goes awry. With a creepy farmhouse and ghosts galore, the toons must work together to face their fears…and a villain they didn't see coming.

added.title: Tooney Ball Lights
added.description: Buster and Sweetie join the Tooney Ball team during Electives Week while Babs and Plucky tackle the basics in Anvils 101, leaving Hamton on a journey to fix his indecisiveness.

added.title: Simply Perfect
added.description: When the kids are about to be subject to school testing with no time to study, Courtney freaks and orders a Brainiac Ray from the back of a comic book that does not work as advertised.

added.title: Bad Seed
added.description: Chef introduces the kids to agriculture by teaching them how to grow plants from seeds. But when Izzy shows her seed too much love, it turns into a monster that terrorizes the class.

added.title: Exit 9B
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are the only ones who can save the park after everyone gets brain washed.

added.title: Starter Pack
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to stop Muscle Man from messing with Thomas.

added.title: Payback/Party Bus
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Wallpaper Man
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: 150-Piece Kit
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he performed a famous drum solo.

added.title: Bald Spot
added.description: Muscle Man wants to hide his bald spot at all costs.

added.title: Guy's Night
added.description: Pops wants to beat the milk challenge to prove he's one of the guys.

added.title: One Pull Up
added.description: Rigby needs to do one pull-up so he can pass the park physical.

added.title: The Christmas Special
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to destroy a gift for Santa to save Christmas.

added.title: Unica's House
added.description: The bears learn about sleepovers when visiting Unica in her hometown.

added.title: The Secret of Chromastone
added.description: Ben meets up with Tetrax but is caught off guard when Tetrax demands that he give him Chromastone. Before Ben has a chance to explain, Tetrax attacks.

added.title: Above and Beyond
added.description: The Plumber's Helpers are called upon by Grandpa Max to rescue him from an abandoned space station where he is being attacked by - Ben!

added.title: Vendetta
added.description: Kevin finds his house ransacked and enlists Ben and Gwen's help to find out who did it and why. They soon cross paths with a deadly criminal.

added.title: The Final Battle Part 1
added.description: Albedo Ben has stolen the Ultimatrix from Azmuth and has used it to kidnap Gwen and Kevin. So Ben goes to face Albedo Ben and rescue his friends.

added.title: The Final Battle Part 2
added.description: A defeated Ben gives up the Omnitrix to save himself and his friends. Powerless, he boards Vilgax's ship for their final battle!

added.title: The Escaping Cows of Sunny Field Farm/Measure For Measure
added.description: Zee's new drone accidentally doubles as a cow caller, and the cows keep leaving the farm to go see it. But how?/Marwyn attempts to make Pretty Big City's largest cookie, but to do so, he'll need a lot of help.

added.title: The Grumpy Effect
added.description: Bluster traps Grumpy in a frustration-inducing labyrinth in an attempt to capture his grumpiness and turn it into the ultimate Bad Seed, which when planted will create new areas of Blusterland. The scheme backfires when Bluster refuses to listen to the warnings of his underlings, and Grumpy's inner kindness turns the Bad Seed into a force for good.

added.title: Forever and Always
added.description: Vivie fears she's jeopardized Nonna's love after she accidentally knocks over Nonna's flower pots. During an adventure in the Enchanted Garden, Barney's big mistakes ruin their fun and Vivie realizes the power of unconditional love.

added.title: Razzle Dazzle Frazzle
added.description: When MOE creates a new, super sparkly vehicle paint, the Batwheels decide to put on a talent show to see who will get a shiny new makeover!

added.title: Pumpkin Panic
added.description: On Halloween Night, Poison Ivy brings all the pumpkins to life, creating an army of Snack-O-Lanterns that eat all the candy. It's up to Redbird and Bam to end her pumpkin panic to save Gotham's Halloween fun, as well as their own.

added.title: Ride Along
added.description: After Kitty the Catmobile saves Bam when he's in a tight spot, Bam decides to take her on a ride along patrol in the hopes of recruiting her as a Batwheel if he can convince her to stop playing long enough to focus on their mission!

added.title: Let's Get Rolling!/A Bit of a Stretch!
added.description: It's MacBarm's croquet tournament and Zee made giant decorations but they're too big to get to the farm./It's the opening day of the skyscraper and the Mechas need to put the sphere on top of the building before the ribbon cutting ceremony.

added.title: Silly Hat Catastrophe!/Zee In A Bottle
added.description: Lloyd is selling silly hats at the factory, but when the hat machine malfunctions it starts raining silly hats on Pretty Big City!/Zee makes a giant rocket ship in a bottle, but things take a turn when he gets stuck inside!

added.title: The Big Whifflesnooze
added.description: Cheer, distracted by other work, doesn't give her complete attention to a problem with the Whiffles. The mistake starts a chain of comical events that results in the Whiffles going into a one-hundred-year sleep that can only be rectified by an ancient chant.

added.title: Neon Beach Party
added.description: Bluster and his Bad Crowd arrive at a lakeside beach for his summer vacation, unaware that the Care Bears are having their vacation on the opposite shore. Trapped inside Bluster's climate-control dome and forced to spend their vacations together, the Bears must find a way to make friends with their ill-tempered neighbors.
